he breeding phenology of Nava's wren has not been documented. Vocalization The male Nava's wren sings \"a varied, often stuttering warble of mellow whistles\" [1]. The female's song is \"an introductory note followed by rapid series of 8 or more loud whistles\" [2]. The species' call is \"a metallic 'tink'\" [3]. Status The IUCN has assessed Nava's wren as Vulnerable \"owing to its small and declining range\" and that its population is estimated to be fewer than 7000 adults. References External links BirdLife Species Factsheet.", "shortSummary": "Nava's wren (Hylorchilus navai) is a species of bird in the family Troglodytidae. It is endemic to Mexico.", "locations": ["韋拉克魯斯州", "恰帕斯州", "瓦哈卡州"], "lat": 19.5272, "lng": -96.9225, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0f/Nava%27a_Wren_-_Chiapas_-_Mexico_S4E7498_%2816548132603%29.jpg/960px-Nava%27a_Wren_-_Chiapas_-_Mexico_S4E7498_%2816548132603%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-hylorchilus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-hylorchilus-navai", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-hylorchilus", "species": "taxonomy-species-hylorchilus-navai"}, "expandable": true, "x": 269.75, "y": -98.95, "z": 167.83}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-hylorchilus", "name": "Hylorchilus", "latinName": "Hylorchilus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Hylorchilus（Hylorchilus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联2种鸟类，如Sumichrast's wren、Nava's wren。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 2, "x": -581.56, "y": 372.39, "z": 18.19}], "links": [{"key": "bird-nava-s-wren-7f96e5a1__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-hylorchilus-navai", "source": "bird-nava-s-wren-7f96e5a1", "target": "taxonomy-species-hylorchilus-navai", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段